<p>A single row in a <span class="script">template.XULElem("rows")</span> element. Each child of the <code>row</code> element is placed in each successive cell of the <span class="script">template.XULElem("grid")</span>. The row with the most child elements determines the number of columns in each row, which may be smaller or larger than the number of <span class="script">template.XULElem("column")</span> elements defined in the grid.</p>
<p>More information is available in the <a title="en/XUL_Tutorial/Grids" href="/en/XUL_Tutorial/Grids">XUL tutorial</a>.</p>
<h3 name="Example">Example</h3>
<p>See <span class="script">template.XULElem("grid")</span> for an example.</p>
